×　　×　　×

Aldebaran: [――Is it crushing? Things like intervals and distances? No, it’s not just those things being crushed, is it?]

△▼△▼△▼△

――God, Buddha, Od Lagna. For as long as I live, I hereby vow to never lament a rainy day.

×　　×　　×

Aldebaran: [――It’s crushing and filling in the insufficient time for thinking, isn’t it? But, Witch Factors aren’t…]

△▼△▼△▼△

――God, Buddha, Od Lagna. For as long as I live, I hereby vow to never gaze upon a rainbow in the company of another.

△▼△▼△▼△

Aldebaran: [――Witch Factors aren’t anything so convenient, now are they?]

That instant, hearing Al’s words as he broke through the encirclement of the Aldebusters to finally stand right before her, a chill ran down Petra’s spine.

She was unable to actually see Al’s eyes, concealed by his steel helmet.. ――Yet, their eyes did meet. That sensation made Petra feel as if her innermost thoughts had been laid bare, a sense of urgency gripping her heart.

It seemed to be exclaiming that somehow, Al possessed a deeper knowledge of the Witch Factor than even Petra.

“Subaru”: [Petra!!]

???: [――Witch ta Flowers Eight!!]

Petra: [――Hk.]

As the command of the cornered husky voice overlapped with the cry of her beloved within her mind, Petra performed Compression on the hesitation that had sprouted within herself, before distancing herself from Al to escape his clutch―― that entire process was Compressed, separating them in an instant.

Aldebaran: [Oi oi, so you can even crush space for yourself…!]

Petra turned to look back, having vanished from right before Al’s eyes, and watched as he clicked his tongue at his failure to catch her.

As Al’s shoulders heaved up and down, his distance from Petra had been set back to square one. Between the two of them as they glared at each other, the Aldebusters, whom Al had exhausted all his efforts to overcome, rose to their feet. In order to reach Petra once again, he would have no choice but to surmount the same hurdles.

However, Petra did not feel as though she had bested him in the slightest.

“Subaru”: [Petra, what Al just said a minute ago…]

Petra: [I know… He really is resetting.]

Hearing the words of the Imaginary Subaru as he floated beside her, Petra narrowed her eyes and gave a nod.

It was not as if she had really been doubting it up to this point, but after witnessing Al’s “Turning Back Time” firsthand, she could not help but feel astonished by how extraordinary it was.

Garfiel’s preemptive strike; the coordinated onslaught of Ram, Flam, and Grassis; the three-pronged enclosure by way of Compression consisting of Gaston, Rachins, and Felt; the obstruction of fifty people mobilized in accordance with Rom-jii’s orders: Al had flawlessly dealt with it all.

He had surmounted all of that with nothing but the most optimal of solutions.

“Subaru”: [Though, our compression of thoughts should be able to produce similar results…]

Petra: [That’s just thinking as hard as possible in order to come up with the right answer. As expected, it’s a bit different from the powers that Subaru and Al-san hold.]

“Subaru”: […If that’s true, I guess I should be this strong, too.]

Scratching his head, “Subaru” lamented his worthlessness. But, Petra did not see it the same way.

Subaru, in his own Subaru way, had confronted his own Authority head-on, and holding tight to the many that ought to have been lost, he had saved Petra and the others. There was not a single shred of worthlessness about him.

And on the other hand to that line of thought――,

Petra: […How many times did you need to restart before you got the chance to reach your hand out towards me?]

As far as Petra was aware, Al’s strength as a warrior was modest―― that was to say, it fell far short of the likes of Ram and Garfiel, on a level that could not even contend with Heinkel. Nevertheless, Al had made sport of the Aldebusters all by himself, and was on the verge of putting them into checkmate.

“Subaru”: [Not even just ten, he might already be on his twentieth try.]

Petra: […I think it might be a bit more.]

Hearing “Subaru’s” naive estimation, Petra anticipated the possibility that it would have actually been ten or twenty times that.

In fact, supposing it was Petra in the position of needing to outmaneuver the Aldebusters, even if she had an Authority that allowed her knowledge of upcoming developments, she was not confident that she would be able to clear it in even a hundred attempts. Not to mention, Al had also managed to sidestep Reinhard, even if he had also needed to borrow the Dragon’s strength to do so.

In order to accomplish such a feat, just how much of one’s heart would one need to kill?

If Al’s “Turning Back Time” was truly what Petra and “Subaru” envisioned, if it was truly a power that came at the cost of Death like Natsuki Subaru’s, then standing there was a dreadful Warlock, masquerading in frivolity.

Al had already conquered the fear and loss of Death―― no, there existed no human capable of conquering that. If it had to be said, it was not conquest, but numbness.

A being who had gone numb to even the instinct of all living things to fear and distance oneself from Death―― that was the secret behind Al’s strength, and what was tied to his absolute nature as a Warlock.

In order to surpass that absoluteness, she too would have no choice but to pay a worthy compensation.

“Subaru”: [――Petra.]

Petra: [It’s alright, Subaru… I’ll be alright.]

He was a being who existed only within her mind.

Only to the Imaginary Subaru, and him alone, had Petra’s secret been revealed; one that had neither been disclosed to any of the Aldebusters, nor to any members of the Emilia Camp.

It was something that the Warlock before her, deeply knowledgeable about Witch Factors as he was, had said to her.

――Upon the one who styled herself the Witch of Tristitia, the likes of a convenient fate smiled not.

Petra: [Even so, something like that isn’t any reason for me to stop.]

Deceiving even herself in such a manner, Petra Leyte―― the Witch of Tristitia, exercised her Authority.

In exchange for interfering with the rules of the world, the existence known as herself was relinquishing its future; no matter how precious and irreplaceable that future was, the newly-birthed Witch did not hesitate whatsoever.

△▼△▼△▼△

――Seven-thousand and eleven.

Petra: [Even so, something like that isn’t any reason for me to stop.]

Seeing Petra’s lips spin those words from afar, Aldebaran could not help but take his hat off. He did not go so far as to actually remove his helmet, but it was to the point that he wanted to do so.

After all, was that not so?

Aldebaran: […Truly, Natsuki Subaru’s one unforgivable guy.]

Grinding his teeth, Aldebaran, in his clash against the Combined Forces―― it seemed like they called themselves the “Aldebusters”. He liked the flair. Though, he did not wish to consider its origin.

Anyway, in his clash against the Aldebusters until this point, he had uncovered that Petra had taken in the Witch Factor of Tristitia, along with the majority of specifics of how its Authority functioned.

As with any battle, it was essential to gather as much accurate information about the opponent as possible.

This was especially true in battles against Sin Archbishops or Witches, and it was often the case that if one confronted such an opponent without a grasp what sort of Authority they were up against, it tended to end in a one-sided killing. ――The ability to overcome being killed in the first encounter was an advantage possessed by both Aldebaran and Natsuki Subaru.

Putting that advantage on full display, Aldebaran had grasped the Authority of Tristitia; it was quite the ridiculous ability. The power to crush―― to Compress space and time, was utterly unrivaled in its adaptability and irksome nature.

To top it all off, it seemed like this Authority was also capable of performing Compression on thoughts, so even within a single second of combat, they were able to think things through thoroughly, and pounce at him one after another with conclusions honed to a razor’s edge. Even with Aldebaran’s Territory, it was a difficult problem that could not be easily solved.

In fact, in order for him to just slip past a mere eleven seconds of combat, he had needed seven-thousand retries.

And yet, even after enduring all that, he had failed to catch ever-important Petra. ――Now that the same amount of distance had been opened between them, it would likely take the same, or an even greater number of attempts to reach her again.

Aldebaran: [Be that as it may, Valga’s affinity with the Authority of Tristitia is just the worst…]

Among the members of the Aldebusters, the figure of Valga Cromwell, who had given him a thorough amount of torment, was present.

While not making any use of the large build he had been blessed with, the resourceful monster had been granted an unlimited amount of time to think freely, allowing him to overwhelm Aldebaran by finding the most optimal solutions.

It was a nightmarish combination, one akin to arming a gorilla with a machine gun. [1]

If Aldebaran were to dance in the palm of Valga’s hand, there was a risk that he could suffer a complete defeat once again. Hence, even if he managed to rob them of their time for thinking, he would not be granted many opportunities for trial and error.

Not to mention, it was not Aldebaran’s intention to keep allowing them to use the Authority of Tristitia.

That was because――,

???: [――The Witch Factor of Tristitia is a defective article. It is a one-of-a-kind Factor that was prepared for the Valiant, so it is not capable of compatibility with any other. From a different angle, however, it could be said that it is compatible with anyone who is willing to pay the compensation, but humans are creatures who can sell off far too much in exchange for their resolve.]

Information about the Witch Factor of Tristitia, told to him by the Witch in the past.

Perhaps because she had many reservations on the topic, the Witch had not been very eager to divulge much concerning the two Witch Factors that ought to be classified as supernumerary, but after running out of patience, her explanations had been surprisingly loquacious.

To make a mostly-irrelevant long story short, the main points were as follows:

――The Witch Factor of Tristitia, would invoke its Authority in exchange for the holder’s will.

――The compensation used by the Witch Factor of Tristitia, could only be paid by the holder.

Aldebaran: [――Natsuki Subaru.]

When his thoughts arrived at that point, Aldebaran once again felt his indignation surge towards Natsuki Subaru.

Of course, Aldebaran did not blind himself to the fact that his own plan of having Petra read the Book of the Dead had played a role in the events that led her to take in the Witch Factor of Tristitia. But, if it was Aldebaran who had created the impetus, then it was Natsuki Subaru who carried a significant portion of the responsibility.

Considering the relationship between Aldebaran and Natsuki Subaru, saying that much was only natural.

The large shadow that hung over Petra’s life was something that had originated from Natsuki Subaru. Aldebaran would not say that he had harbored malicious intent, nor did he believe that to be the case, but the influence he had over her went without saying. And not limited to just Petra, it could be said that he had exhibited a certain fateful power over even the Aldebusters―― no, over many scenarios even preceding this battle. [――Co] Regardless, it was a bit ironic to call it a fateful power. After all, even though it was none other than Natsuki Subaru and Aldebaran who despised fate the most, [――m] it would have been no exaggeration to say that their actions were what decided fate. [――p] Upon thinking that, what flashed through Aldebaran’s mind were the words of the woman of such brilliant crimson. Back then, [――re] the words of praise she had spoken to him in their final time together, were attempting to scorch Aldebaran’s heart. Deliberately, he averted his gaze, and plugged his ears. [――ss] At this stage, it was far too late for him to reflect on his own actions. That which now sustained Aldebaran was not she whom he had lost, but the Oath he had sworn to his Teacher. [――A] The purpose for which Aldebaran had been born, that which he had been made into Aldebaran to accomplish, the culmination of all that was now being put to the test. For that reason, he had not the time to halt his tracks and think―― wait, wait wait wait. Isn’t this too long? Just a moment’s pause, a chance to take a deep breath before the battle resumed. [――go] That’s what it ought to have been. His opponents did not wish to allow him any breathers. He also did not want to grant his opponents much time. [――n] Even though they should have been at such a consensus, how could Aldebaran be engaging in such deep thought―― [――y].

Shit. This is strange. What is this? What did she say? Far in the distance, he could tell that Petra had moved her lips. One syllable at a time, he would pick up the sound those lips had weaved. Everything that had been thrown in while he was thinking, he picked it all up, and collected it together. Slow. Sluggish. Far too laggard. Collect the meaning, collect the significance, collect the intent. ――. ――――. ――――. It was no use. He could not silence his thoughts. He would just have to think. “Compress”? Crushing, huh? Crushing, what exactly? “Agony”?  Pain? Anguish? Suffering… suffering? Concerns, thoughts, unraveling. Fuck, she got me. They’ve been Compressed.

――My thoughts, they’ve been Compressed!!

△▼△▼△▼△

――God, Buddha, Od Lagna. For as long as I live, I hereby vow to never divulge this important secret.

△▼△▼△▼△

Petra: [――Compress Agony.]

A Compression of thoughts by way of the Authority of Tristitia―― a powerful buff effect consisting of speeding up her allies’ thoughts, omitting any need for discussion, and allowing them to take the most optimal measures after thorough consideration from everyone; conferring that unto Al was one of the countermeasures Petra had prepared against him.

Petra: [When you have too many things to think about, your head will get punctured.]

While it might have been presumptuous, Petra prided herself on being the third most knowledgeable in the world about the “Turning Back Time” of Return by Death, just behind Subaru and Al.

Petra had acquired that scholarship from the vicarious experience of the Death tasted by Subaru, so she had discovered a way to nullify―― no, to overheat the seemingly invincible Authority of Al.

That being, to overload his mind with accelerated thoughts.

In the past, when the Royal Selection had first commenced, Subaru had gotten into a fight and parted with Emilia in the Royal Capital, and the large amount of stress and mental burden that came as a result had worn down his heart.

Inadvertently, Rem’s devotion and his anger toward the Sin Archbishop had given him the chance to get back on his feet, but it was a fact that he had lost his will to fight, ending up as an empty husk, even if only temporarily. ――She would recreate that effect.

Since Al had already gone numb to the fear of Death, it was likely that he would not lose heart no matter how many Deaths he accreted.

Nonetheless, even if he had decided to make an enemy of the world, Al was still human.

Rifts would form in his mind, and he would be unable to avoid having it come apart at the seams. She would make it so.

For that purpose, no matter what she needed to give up in exchange――,

Aldebaran: [――Expand Territory, Matrix Redefinition.]

While tormented by the acceleration of thoughts, Al could be heard silently voicing those words.

His mind might have been under a high burden, but this situation was still a double-edged sword. The odds were even; either Al’s heart would give out from extreme exhaustion, or he would make full use of the Compression of his mind like the Aldebusters to fend off Petra and the others.

Hence, the battle from this point onward was do-or-die for the Aldebusters in the truest sense――,

Petra: [――Everyone! It’s only just getting started! Don’t lose focus!]

Everyone: [――YEAHH!!]

At Petra’s encouragement, her allies whose interactions had been Compressed cheered in response.

Finding that to be reliable, she was about to look out over the decisive battle against Al starting from square one―― then she noticed.

Among those who had just given her that reassuring response, there was someone whose voice she had not heard.

It was possible that they had just missed the timing. But, feeling a peculiar sense of discomfort in that, Petra glanced over in that direction, searching for the figure of the person who had given no response.

And then, she found him.

Petra: [――Rom-ojiisan?]

She found the figure of the Great Strategist who had given no response, the old giant who bore the duty of observing the battlefield and giving timely and accurate commands, his eyes having gone white as he slowly collapsed onto the ground.

△▼△▼△▼△

――Let us rewind the clock to mere moments prior.

Aldebaran: [――Expand Territory, Matrix Redefinition.]

Indeed, upon hearing Aldebaran declare those words, a tremor ran through Rom-jii’s large shoulders.

Upon bearing witness to the sight of Aldebaran standing still before the Combined Forces, Rom-jii felt an unnatural discomposure settle within him, causing him to stiffen as he motionlessly widened his eyes.

Rom-jii was well aware of Petra’s stratagem that applied the Authority of Tristitia.

Her strategy revolved around accelerating Aldebaran’s thoughts, placing a burden on his mind to fully exhaust him in one fell swoop. Rom-jii had also deemed it a necessary step in order to take down Aldebaran, given his ability to perform something akin to “Turning Back Time”, and thus he had promised to cooperate with it.

He had harbored some apprehensions towards speeding up Aldebaran’s thoughts, but since they were also Compressing their own thoughts to arrive at the best possible answers, he accepted that it would just boil down to their overall strength. If that was their course of action, Rom-jii also felt like he could lend his own strength.

And as it so happened, the battle against Aldebaran had gone just about exactly how Rom-jii had expected it to.

His comrades mobilized quickly, and successfully managed to drive Aldebaran into a corner. ――But, much to the shock of Rom-jii, his discomposure would commence from that moment onward.

Aldebaran: [――Expand Territory, Matrix Redefinition.]

Indeed, as Aldebaran declared so, Rom-jii’s position shifted in an instant. ――No, it was not only Rom-jii whose position had shifted; the positions of Aldebaran, Felt, and everyone else participating in the battle returned to where they had stood a mere ten-odd seconds prior, and recommenced from there.

And, Rom-jii had already experienced that same phenomenon five times now――,

Rom: [――What in tarnation, is this situation?]

Craning his neck all around, Rom-jii gathered that he was amidst the same scenery he had witnessed five times now, and wrung those words out in a solemn tone.

Nobody other than Rom-jii had noticed the abnormality of this situation.

Petra: [――Everyone! It’s only just getting started! Don’t lose focus!]

Everyone: [――YEAHH!!]

As proof of that, everyone other than Rom-jii responded to Petra’s rousing voice of leadership.

Then, they all faced Aldebaran, and sprung at him in unison.

Felt: [Rom-jii! Give us orders!]

Failing to notice his discomposure, Felt searched for a position to attack from with Star Staff in hand. The allies other than Felt who also possessed techniques that could serve as the deciding factor were also running while awaiting Rom-jii’s commands.

Watching their backs, Rom-jii gulped down his bitter saliva, and shouted out commands differing to the ones from just before――,

Aldebaran: [――Expand Territory, Matrix Redefinition.]

――Now for the sixth time, the final battle against Aldebaran commenced.

 

Translation Note:

[1] – 鬼に金棒めいた is a Japanese idiom along the lines of “Giving a metal bat to an Oni”. Essentially saying to make a strong thing even stronger. I have used all of my brainpower to generate an English equivalent to capture this sentiment. As some of you might know, this text is Japanese, and Japanese I can handle just fine. But Japanese with cultural specific idioms is like a chimp with a machine gun!
